captions.text: -Hi.

We're Brooke and
Bailey, and today, we

are going to be doing a fall
to winter fashion video.

And we have been really
excited for fall and winter.

Down here in Texas,
it's still not cold,

but we're busting out the
sweaters and coats anyways,

because we're getting in
that fally, wintry mood,

and we just want to
wear the clothes for it.
-Yeah.

So we have picked out a couple
of our favorite fall and winter

clothing items, and we are
going to show you guys how

to transition from fall
outfits to winter outfits.

-This outfit is definitely my
most favorite fall outfit ever.

To start off, I have
my vivid red boots

that I bought from
Old Navy, and I also

have these red striped
tights that it also
bought from Old Navy.

Matching vivid tights
and boots together
is very in for the fall.

Next, I have my
black tanktop dress
that I bought from Old Navy.

And then I just pulled
over this jean jacket

that I got a little while
ago from Forever 21.

And then I have this black
and white polka dot scarf

that I also bought
from Old Navy, just
to keep me warm in the winter.
My bracelets is from Forever 21.

It's just a red
rosette bracelet.

And this just pulls in
the boots and the tights

and brings the whole
outfit together.

-Starting at the very
bottom with my shoes,

I got these at
Uptown Cheapskate.

That's actually a thrift
store here in Texas.

And I showed you guys these
shoes in my other thrift shop
fashion video.

My jeans are also from
Uptown Cheapskate.

They are just a dark
wash skinny jeans.

My blue long sleeved
undershirt is from Target.

And I'll either wear this
under for an undershirt or just
for layers for warmth.

And my auburn vest with the gold
buttons is from American Eagle.

And I just chose to scarf
from Dressing Your Truth

to go with it, because I
thought it went really well.

During the
wintertime, just throw

on a jacket and
some gloves and you

will be nice and warm
for the cold weather.

-This is my next fall
to winter outfit.

To stand off, I have these super
duper ooper cute ankle boots.

I'm loving the
ankle boots lately.

And I just got these gray
ones from Aeropostle.

Next, I have my
tribal print pants.

Holy cow, let me just say,
tribal print is adorable.

So I found these Aeropostle
and fell in love,

and the boots just
match perfectly.

In case you get cold
in the wintertime,

I usually just pull over
a black leather jacket.
I got this one from Forever 21.
I love the V at the bottom.

And it just keeps me warm in
the winter and cold weather.

For my jewelry, I have my
silver watch from Fossil,

and my earrings
are from Claire's.

That store is the best for any
kind of jewelry that you want,
winter or fall.

For my hair, I've just
done a simple pancake
dutch braid into a braid.

If you want to see
more of our tutorials,
go to Cute Girls Hairstyles.
-Boo!
Hello, people.

This is my second outfit, and
I absolutely love this outfit.
It is one of my favorites.

My shoes are just
black Doc Martins,
and I got them from Aeropostle.

And I was so excited when
we decided to buy these,

because I've been wanting
a pair for a long time.

I bought my pants
at American Eagle,
and they were pre-ripped.

So I just absolutely love
wearing them to give myself
kind of a more rugged look.

Vests are really
in right now, so we

went and bought this
black leather vest

with these adorable zip
up pockets on the sides.
I absolutely love them.

And it is from
Aeropostle, and the shirt

underneath with the
awesome sunglasses
is also from Aeropostle.
Look at me with my sunglasses.

This cute black cross
ring is from Forever 21.

I got a little wild, though,
but I really like it.

My salmon knit beanie
is from Aeropostle,

and I really like
it with this outfit,

because it just gave the whole
thing a little pop of color.

If you get cold in
this outfit, you

can just switch your
black leather vest

for a long sleeved
jacket and you'll

be nice and toasty
for the wintertime.

-Thank you guys so
much for watching

our fall to winter
fashion video.

Don't forget to follow us on
Twitter at BrookeAndBailey.

-Make sure to comment below on
which outfit was your favorite.

And don't forget to
watch next week's video.
Bye.
-Oh there she goes.

They're actually
doing remarkably well.

A few days ago, they
couldn't even hardly sit up,

and now they're
just sitting up like

crazy except for a few
tumbles once in a while.

They like to steal
each other's toys.
Brooklyn.
Hi.
Hi, sweetie.
Bailey.
Hey.
Hi.
Are you Mommy's girls?
